Tyler Marenyi (born October 11, 1990), better known by his stage name Nghtmre (stylized as in all caps; pronounced "nightmare"), is an American DJ and electronic dance music producer based in Los Angeles, California.
He debuted at EDC Las Vegas 2015, which was his first festival performance.
In 2016, he released his EP titled Nghtmre which had charted on Billboard's Top Dance/Electronic Albums chart.
An official music video for the song was released by Francis on May 9, 2016 via YouTube.
In 2017 Marenyi was in the lineup at Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival.
2019: Dillon Francis and Alison Wonderland — "Lost My Mind" (Nghtmre Remix)
2021: Illenium and Matt Maeson — "Heavenly Side" (Nghtmre Remix)
